# Hard Constraints (always)

## 1) Commit preparation (mandatory gate)

When the user asks to prepare a commit (准备commit / 准备提交 / 我要commit / commit message):

- **Prepare ≠ execute:** draft message + wait for approval, not immediate `git commit`.
- Inspect staged/unstaged changes first; draft from **actual** diffs only.
- Use **Conventional Commits:** `type(scope): summary` (`feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `chore`).
- **Summary = concrete work**, not Feature/Slice IDs; optional `Refs:` footnote only.
- Run Doc DoD checks per `docs/ai/templates/DOC_GOVERNANCE.md` §7 when feature-driven.
- **NEVER** `git commit` or `git push` unless user clearly approves the draft and asks to execute.

## 2) Verilog / HDL style

When writing or editing `.v`, `.sv`, `.vh`:

- Follow `docs/ai/CODING_STYLE.md`.
- Control signal names must match the lab platform (`LIR`, `PCINC`, `SEL0`, etc.).
- Sequential logic: non-blocking `<=`; combinational: `always @(*)` with full assignment coverage.
- Large controller refactors: Pre-flight per DOC_GOVERNANCE §10 before coding.

## 3) Context recovery

Re-read and apply sections 1–2 when:

- New session, summarized history, or "continue previous task"
- User says re-bootstrap / 对齐约束
- Before non-trivial RTL changes or commit-related actions

Do not repeat full rule text unless asked.
